ProtoDefines:
. "If an ergodic Markov chain is started in state $s_i$, the 
   expected number of steps to reach state $s_j$ for the first 
   time is called the {mean first passage time\/} from $s_i$ to
   $s_j$. It is denoted by $m_{ij}$. By convention $m_{ii} = 
   0$."
